Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content: not sure how to modify the `inherit type descriptor` to the new `asn_TPRE-DEscripter_t` structure

Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content:
before it was ```c
static void
cost_3_inherit_TYPE_descriptor(asn_TYPE_descriptor_t *td) {
    td->free_struct    = asn_DEF_NativeInteger.free_struct;```

Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content: this however segfaults:

Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content:
```c
static void
cost_3_inherit_TYPE_descriptor(asn_TYPE_descriptor_t *td) {
    td->op->free_struct    = asn_DEF_NativeInteger.op->free_struct;```

Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content:
should it be ```c
 ... = &asn_DEF_NativeInteger.op->free_struct;``` ??

Author: Chris - Monkins#5278
Content: Follow up...  doing  `td->op = asn_DEF_NativeInteger.op;` has fixed it

Author: mediast#1110
Content:
When launching a new smartchain, we used the parameters documented here:

https://komodoplatform.com/18-ways-to-customize-blockchain/

We included ac_Reward(s) parameter as documented in the above article, but it appears that the correct parameter should've been ac_reward...

The -ac_CCenable parameter does not appear to work, as ALL Antara modules have been activated (not just the ones we desired).  OR are these parameters case-sensitive?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: case sensitive

Author: mediast#1110
Content: The -ac_CCenable parameter may've also failed because we did this: -ac_CCenable=0xe3,0xeb,0xe4,0xf1,0xea,0xec,0xf0,0xf2 instead of ac_ccenable=227,228, etc..

Author: mediast#1110
Content: But also because the parameters are case sensitive..

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: case sensitive, use decimal

Author: mediast#1110
Content: Thank you.  I was mislead by this "The eval codes can be found here" on the aforementioned article, but I found the ac_ccenable=227,228 example under docs

Author: mediast#1110
Content: Perhaps the article can be corrected (case sensitivity, ac_reward(s))
